A powerful cyclone hit Bangladesh's southern coast, causing severe destruction.
Officials in both Bangladesh and India evacuated hundreds of thousands of people.
The storm, named Cyclone Sidr, killed at least 41 people and forced the evacuation of 650,000 villagers.
The United States and Germany offered emergency relief aid to assist in recovery efforts.
The cyclone left a trail of devastation, with reports of rising death tolls and widespread impact on coastal areas.
The United Nations World Food Program allocated food supplies to feed 400,000 victims.
Efforts are ongoing to provide assistance and support to those affected.
